Welcome to the study. You will first complete a short volume calibration and headphone check.

Please make sure you are in a quiet listening environment, that you are wearing headphones, and that your computer's volume is turned on.

The volume calibration will be first.

You will hear a thirty-second noise. Please adjust your computer's volume so that this noise is being presented at a comfortable level.

You will now complete a short headphone check.

On each trial, you will hear three tones. One of these tones will be quieter than the others. Your task is to identify whether the quiet tone occured first, second, or third.

There are six trials in total.
The volume calibration and headphone check are now complete.

In this part of the study, you will hear sounds similar to those you just heard.

Please focus on these sounds, as you may be asked questions about them later.

Occasionally, the sounds will pause for up to two seconds. When this happens, please press SPACEBAR as quickly as you can.
This helps ensure that you are paying attention to the sounds.

You will now listen to longer sound sequences.

Each sound sequence will last about 16 seconds.

On each trial, you will be given a TARGET SOUND. Your task is to listen very carefully for this sound.

Every time you hear the TARGET SOUND, you will press the SPACEBAR as quickly and accurately as you can.

It is very important that you make your responses as quickly and accurately as possible.

To help you make your responses, you will be able to listen to the TARGET SOUND at the beginning of each trial.

There will be 36 total trials.

Note: This is meant to be a difficult task. We simply want you to try your best.

To replay the TARGET SOUND, press P.
